---
import PageShell from '../../components/PageShell.astro';
import CTABox from '../../components/CTABox.astro';
import ComparisonTable from '../../components/ComparisonTable.astro';

const title = "Insurance for International Athletic Trainers | Compare Expat Plans";
const description = "Health insurance guide for Athletic Trainers working internationally, covering athletic training careers abroad, sports medicine, and global team opportunities.";
const headline = "Insurance for International Athletic Trainers";
const subheadline = "Coverage solutions for Athletic Trainers working abroad, providing sports medicine internationally, and pursuing careers across professional teams, sports organizations, and athletic facilities worldwide.";
const canonicalPath = "/guides/athletic-trainer-insurance";
const heroBackgroundImage = "/images/guides/athletic-trainer-insurance-hero.png";

const tocItems = [
  { id: 'overview', label: 'Overview' },
  { id: 'coverage-needs', label: 'Coverage Needs' },
  { id: 'work-settings', label: 'Work Settings' },
  { id: 'credentials', label: 'Credentials' },
  { id: 'occupational-health', label: 'Occupational Health' },
  { id: 'work-demands', label: 'Work Demands' },
  { id: 'career-considerations', label: 'Career Considerations' },
  { id: 'faqs', label: 'FAQs' },
  { id: 'next-steps', label: 'Next Steps' },
];
---

<PageShell
  title={title}
  description={description}
  headline={headline}
  subheadline={subheadline}
  canonicalPath={canonicalPath}
  heroBackgroundImage={heroBackgroundImage}
  tocItems={tocItems}
>
  <article class="prose prose-lg max-w-none">

    <section id="overview">
      <h2>International Athletic Trainer Careers</h2>
      <p>
        Athletic Trainers prevent, diagnose, and treat muscle and bone injuries in athletes. International athletic training careers offer opportunities to work with elite sports teams, support athletes at international competitions, and provide sports medicine expertise in global sporting contexts.
      </p>
      <p>
        International athletic training opportunities exist through professional sports teams abroad, Olympic and Paralympic programs, international sports federations, sports medicine clinics, and organizations supporting athletes at international competitions and events.
      </p>
      <p>
        This guide addresses insurance considerations for Athletic Trainers working abroad across professional teams, sports organizations, and athletic facilities worldwide.
      </p>
    </section>

    <section id="coverage-needs">
      <h2>Coverage Needs for Athletic Trainers</h2>

      <ComparisonTable
        columns={[
          { key: 'need', header: 'Coverage Need' },
          { key: 'why', header: 'Why It Matters' },
          { key: 'typical', header: 'Coverage Situation?' },
        ]}
        rows={[
          { need: 'General health coverage', why: 'Professional health maintenance', typical: 'Variable by employer' },
          { need: 'Physical injury coverage', why: 'Active work demands', typical: 'Important for role' },
          { need: 'Travel medical', why: 'Competition travel', typical: 'Essential for sports' },
          { need: 'Professional liability', why: 'Medical treatment liability', typical: 'Critical to verify' },
          { need: 'Ergonomic coverage', why: 'Treatment positioning', typical: 'Consider for long-term' },
          { need: 'Disability coverage', why: 'Physical career aspects', typical: 'Review carefully' },
        ]}
      />

      <h3>Healthcare Provider Role</h3>
      <p>
        Athletic trainers provide medical care including injury assessment, treatment, and rehabilitation. Professional liability coverage is essential given the healthcare nature of athletic training work. Verify whether employers provide liability coverage or if personal coverage is needed.
      </p>
      <p>
        Athletic training involves hands-on treatment that carries both physical demands for the trainer and liability considerations for the care provided.
      </p>

      <h3>Travel Requirements</h3>
      <p>
        Athletic trainers travel extensively with teams to competitions, training camps, and events. Travel medical coverage is essential for sports medicine professionals accompanying athletes internationally.
      </p>
    </section>

    <section id="work-settings">
      <h2>Coverage by Work Setting</h2>

      <h3>Professional Teams</h3>
      <p>
        Sports organization employment. Team benefits variable. Travel intensive. Teams offer exposure.
      </p>

      <h3>National Federations</h3>
      <p>
        National team programs. Federation or government benefits. Elite level support. Federations offer prestige.
      </p>

      <h3>Sports Medicine Clinics</h3>
      <p>
        Clinical settings. Clinic benefits. Treatment-focused. Clinics offer stability.
      </p>

      <h3>Universities</h3>
      <p>
        College athletic programs. University benefits. Student-athlete focus. Universities offer resources.
      </p>

      <h3>Events</h3>
      <p>
        Competition and event coverage. Contract-based often. Temporary assignments. Events offer variety.
      </p>
    </section>

    <CTABox
      title="Coverage for Athletic Trainers"
      description="Compare international health plans designed for Athletic Trainers working abroad across professional teams, sports organizations, and athletic facilities worldwide."
      buttonText="Compare Athletic Trainer Plans"
      buttonHref="/"
      variant="highlight"
    />

    <section id="credentials">
      <h2>Credentials and Professional Recognition</h2>

      <h3>Athletic Training Degree</h3>
      <p>
        Masters in Athletic Training. Professional degree. Foundation credential. Degree enables certification.
      </p>

      <h3>BOC Certification</h3>
      <p>
        Board of Certification credential. ATC designation. Required for practice. Certification enables employment.
      </p>

      <h3>International Recognition</h3>
      <p>
        Recognition varies by country. May need additional credentials. Research destination requirements. Recognition not universal.
      </p>

      <h3>Continuing Education</h3>
      <p>
        BOC CE requirements. Skill maintenance. Current practice. CE maintains certification.
      </p>
    </section>

    <section id="occupational-health">
      <h2>Occupational Health Considerations</h2>

      <h3>Physical Demands</h3>
      <p>
        Treatment provision. Taping and wrapping. Rehabilitation assistance. Physical work demands.
      </p>

      <h3>Travel</h3>
      <p>
        Extensive travel with teams. Competition attendance. Time zones and schedules. Travel intensive.
      </p>

      <h3>Event Demands</h3>
      <p>
        Long hours during events. Competition stress. On-call availability. Event demands intense.
      </p>

      <h3>Emotional</h3>
      <p>
        Athlete injuries. Career-ending diagnoses. Team pressure. Emotional support valuable.
      </p>
    </section>

    <section id="work-demands">
      <h2>Managing Work Demands</h2>

      <h3>Prevention</h3>
      <p>
        Injury prevention programs. Conditioning guidance. Risk reduction. Prevention protects athletes.
      </p>

      <h3>Treatment</h3>
      <p>
        Acute injury care. Taping and bracing. Modality application. Treatment enables return.
      </p>

      <h3>Rehabilitation</h3>
      <p>
        Recovery protocols. Progressive exercise. Return-to-play management. Rehabilitation restores function.
      </p>

      <h3>Coordination</h3>
      <p>
        Physician communication. Coaching coordination. Healthcare team collaboration. Coordination ensures comprehensive care.
      </p>
    </section>

    <section id="career-considerations">
      <h2>Career Considerations</h2>

      <h3>Global Sports</h3>
      <p>
        International teams need athletic trainers. Sports medicine valued globally. Competition support. Opportunities exist worldwide.
      </p>

      <h3>Career Paths</h3>
      <p>
        Staff to head athletic trainer. Sports medicine director. Private practice. Education. Multiple paths available.
      </p>

      <h3>Credential Portability</h3>
      <p>
        ATC not universally recognized. May need additional qualifications. Research destination. Portability varies.
      </p>

      <h3>Team Integration</h3>
      <p>
        Part of sports medicine team. Physician collaboration. Coach relationships. Integration essential.
      </p>
    </section>

    <section id="faqs">
      <h2>Frequently Asked Questions</h2>

      <div class="space-y-6">
        <div class="bg-white border border-neutral-200 rounded-lg p-6">
          <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-neutral-900 mt-0 mb-2">I'm an athletic trainer considering international work. What should I know?</h3>
          <p class="text-neutral-600 mb-0">
            Credential recognition varies. Team positions may provide coverage. Professional liability critical. Research specific opportunities.
          </p>
        </div>

        <div class="bg-white border border-neutral-200 rounded-lg p-6">
          <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-neutral-900 mt-0 mb-2">Do professional teams provide coverage?</h3>
          <p class="text-neutral-600 mb-0">
            Varies by team and league. Contract terms determine. May include medical staff. Verify before accepting.
          </p>
        </div>

        <div class="bg-white border border-neutral-200 rounded-lg p-6">
          <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-neutral-900 mt-0 mb-2">Is professional liability important?</h3>
          <p class="text-neutral-600 mb-0">
            Critical for healthcare provision. Treatment involves liability. Verify employer provides or arrange personal. Essential protection.
          </p>
        </div>

        <div class="bg-white border border-neutral-200 rounded-lg p-6">
          <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-neutral-900 mt-0 mb-2">Will my ATC credential work internationally?</h3>
          <p class="text-neutral-600 mb-0">
            Not universally recognized. Some countries have equivalents. May need local credentials. Research destination requirements.
          </p>
        </div>

        <div class="bg-white border border-neutral-200 rounded-lg p-6">
          <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-neutral-900 mt-0 mb-2">Is travel coverage important?</h3>
          <p class="text-neutral-600 mb-0">
            Essential for team positions. Competition travel extensive. International events common. Prioritize travel medical.
          </p>
        </div>

        <div class="bg-white border border-neutral-200 rounded-lg p-6">
          <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-neutral-900 mt-0 mb-2">What's the career outlook?</h3>
          <p class="text-neutral-600 mb-0">
            Sports medicine valued globally. Professional teams need support. Olympic programs active. Opportunities for qualified professionals.
          </p>
        </div>
      </div>
    </section>

    <section id="next-steps">
      <h2>Next Steps</h2>
      <p>
        Start by researching credential recognition in your target destination. Verify professional liability coverage provisions. Ensure travel medical coverage for team travel. Consider physical demands and long-term career sustainability.
      </p>
      <p>
        Athletic Trainers keep athletes healthy and competing worldwide. Your coverage should support sports medicine careers—addressing liability concerns, enabling competition travel, and protecting your health across athletic training positions worldwide.
      </p>
    </section>

    <CTABox
      title="Protect Your Athletic Training Career"
      description="Compare international health plans designed for Athletic Trainers working abroad across professional teams, sports organizations, and athletic facilities worldwide."
      buttonText="Compare Plans Now"
      buttonHref="/"
      variant="highlight"
    />

  </article>
</PageShell>
